[DhtmlXQ_comment0]sg 20120307 2010 jjls Pan Zhenbo L Zheng Weitong||This is a short game played in 2010/9/29. I chose this game to show how a tiny, not very obvious mistake in the opening can have drastic consequences. It is also an introduction of two up and coming players in China.||Taking Red is Master Pan Zhenbo. Master Pan was born in 1974 and hails from Liaoning but he is representing Shandong province now. He was awarded the title of Xiangqi Master in 1994 by coming in 10th place in the National Chinese Xiangqi Championships, and improving his placings to 4th place in 2004, before improving to 2nd place in 2005. His greatest claim to fame was winning the 2007 Singles Tournament held by the AXF.||Taking Black is Master Zheng Weitong from Chengdu, Sichuan. He is one of China's pride. Born in 1994,he is also one of the youngest Xq stars. Zheng's first claim to fame was in 2006 when he won the under 12 Chinese National Championbships, and again in 2008 when he won the under 14, and again in 2009 in the under 16. He made Xiangqi master in 2009 by coming 11th place in the 2009 Chinese National Singles Championship.[/DhtmlXQ_comment0]
