[DhtmlXQ_comment56]And the young Master Zheng shows great patience by attempting to further simplify the game to an sure-win endgame for him. With this move, he also prevents any chance of possible mischief when the red cannon moves away for a discovered check. ||If red does not accept the exchange and plays R5-1, the red pawn is lost and all hope is lost for red.[/DhtmlXQ_comment56]
[DhtmlXQ_comment58]And the red pawn is pinned temporarily to the sidelines. There is nowhere it can move and it is basically functionless.||The remaining black and red pawn take the center stage now. ||If red were able to destroy that black pawn, and even charge his pawn across the river, he could still force a draw.||Black understands the gravity of the situation and  a fight for control of the pawns erupts.[/DhtmlXQ_comment58]
